just_use main.go

# label: ONE_OFF
# role: encodes domain knowledge

The mux and the wireDB() step. Every package that needs the DB gets
*sql.DB injected here via package-level vars; this is how we break the
obvious import cycle (auth ← channels ← flags ← events all wired to the
same DB). RenderMarkdown is injected the same way to avoid a markdown-
package import cycle.

Entry point: GOPHER_CONFIG → loadConfig → initDB → seedData (demo only) →
buildMux → ListenAndServe. Demo mode auto-sets GOPHER_RESET_DB=1 and seeds
test data; prod never does either. Rate limiting runs on authenticated
non-poll requests only — /api/v1/events is exempt because polling at idle
should not burn a user's window.
